        "comment": "The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust and will soften quickly. In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. <br/> As a consequence of warming, the activity of moist and wet avalanches will increase. This applies especially on very steep sunny slopes at intermediate and high altitudes, and in steep rocky terrain. <br/> <br/> Also below approximately 2700 m and on very steep shady slopes individual medium-sized natural wet avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation.",
